Leaders of <ENAMEX TYPE="ORG">the European Union</ENAMEX> and <ENAMEX TYPE="CARDINAL">five</ENAMEX> <ENAMEX TYPE="NORP">Balkan</ENAMEX> states meet in <ENAMEX TYPE="GPE">Zagreb</ENAMEX> <ENAMEX TYPE="DATE">today</ENAMEX> to hail a new era of cooperation in a region that has been torn by conflict .
<ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Douglas Paction</ENAMEX> has more on the story .
The summit , which is being sponsored by <ENAMEX TYPE="ORG">the European Union</ENAMEX> , is meant to show the <ENAMEX TYPE="NORP">Balkan</ENAMEX> states that the <ENAMEX TYPE="ORG">EU</ENAMEX> is preparing to welcome them into the <ENAMEX TYPE="NORP">European</ENAMEX> family .
<ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Christina Gayat</ENAMEX> , a spokeswoman for <ENAMEX TYPE="ORG">EU</ENAMEX> Foreign Policy Chief <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Javier Solana</ENAMEX> , says the summit has an important symbolic value .
I think it will be the occasion to welcome at the highest level of <ENAMEX TYPE="ORG">the European Union</ENAMEX> under the highest level of the region , the very dramatic changes that have occurred since <ENAMEX TYPE="DATE">the beginning of the year</ENAMEX> and to further consolidate democracy and reconciliation .
Analysts say , <ENAMEX TYPE="DATE">last month 's</ENAMEX> formal ouster of <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Slobodan Milosevic</ENAMEX> in presidential elections in <ENAMEX TYPE="GPE">Yugoslavia</ENAMEX> was a pivotal event for the region .
The leaders of the <ENAMEX TYPE="CARDINAL">five</ENAMEX> <ENAMEX TYPE="NORP">Balkan</ENAMEX> states of the summit , <ENAMEX TYPE="GPE">Yugoslavia</ENAMEX> , <ENAMEX TYPE="GPE">Croatia</ENAMEX> , <ENAMEX TYPE="GPE">Macedonia</ENAMEX> , <ENAMEX TYPE="GPE">Albania</ENAMEX> and <ENAMEX TYPE="GPE">Bosnia</ENAMEX> are expected to adopt a declaration calling for a political dialogue and regional economic cooperation .
<ENAMEX TYPE="ORG">The European Union</ENAMEX> is offering a <ENAMEX TYPE="MONEY">3.9 billion - dollar</ENAMEX> financial aid program to help the region , which has long been devastated by civil conflict , economic collapse and political isolation .
In return the <ENAMEX TYPE="NORP">Balkan</ENAMEX> leaders will be called upon to continue moving toward democracy and a market economy .
The leaders will also be asked to take steps to fight organized crime , drug trafficking , and money laundering .
Also at the <ENAMEX TYPE="GPE">Zagreb</ENAMEX> summit , <ENAMEX TYPE="GPE">Macedonia</ENAMEX> is expected to sign an association and stabilization pact with <ENAMEX TYPE="ORG">the European Union</ENAMEX> .
This is a <ENAMEX TYPE="ORDINAL">first</ENAMEX> step on the long road to full <ENAMEX TYPE="ORG">EU</ENAMEX> membership .
